{"title":"Syncros Fraser & Hixon iC SL bars bring fully-integrated cockpit routing to XC and trail MTB","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/11/02/syncros-fraser-hixon-ic-sl-bars-bring-fully-integrated-cockpit-routing-to-xc-and-trail-mtb/","date":1635883529000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081957/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_carbon-Syncros-cockpit.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081957/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_carbon-Syncros-cockpit-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Scott Spark RC &amp; 900 XC trail mountain bikes, light fully-integrated cross-country MTB,&nbsp;carbon cockpit\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081957/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_carbon-Syncros-cockpit-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081957/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_carbon-Syncros-cockpit-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081957/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_carbon-Syncros-cockpit-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081957/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_carbon-Syncros-cockpit-768x576.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081957/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_carbon-Syncros-cockpit-696x522.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081957/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_carbon-Syncros-cockpit-1068x801.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081957/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_carbon-Syncros-cockpit-560x420.jpg 560w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081957/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_carbon-Syncros-cockpit-80x60.jpg 80w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081957/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_carbon-Syncros-cockpit-265x198.jpg 265w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081957/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_carbon-Syncros-cockpit.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-276118\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Syncros is expanding the integrated internal cable routing, one-piece carbon bar &amp; stem cockpit concept to mountain bikes with their latest Fraser iC SL &amp; Hixon iC SL bars. They aren’t the first 1-piece MTB bar+stem combos, not even the first for Syncros. And they don’t get full internal cable routing yet since pretty much only <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/?s=magura+MCi\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Magura MCi</a> &amp; <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/02/09/dangerholm-drops-sub-10kg-hyper-spark-xc-dream-bike-w-stratospheric-spec-list/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Dangerholm</a> have tried to route mountain bike brakes inside your bar.</p><p>But as more and more XC &amp; trail bikes start to shift cable routing into MTB frames through the headset, these Syncros Fraser &amp; Hixon iC bars start to signal more integration on mountain bikes too…</p><h2>Syncros Fraser &amp; Hixon iC SL integrated cockpit MTB bars</h2><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/PaI947-AfH4?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></p><p>We first rode Syncros’ new one-piece carbon Fraser iC SL XC integrated handlebar cockpit with its unique internal cable routing stem setup when Scott launched their <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/06/09/2022-scott-spark-gets-bold-new-redesign-as-a-slack-fast-fully-integrated-120mm-xc-bike/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">all-new Spark</a> earlier past summer. Now that cross-country Fraser adds several new mountain bike bar siblings, from World Cup XC to downcountry. Now, there’s even a new pair of Hixon iC SL trail bike bars too, perfect for the new <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/11/02/bold-linkin-hidden-shock-carbon-trail-bike-is-back-with-all-new-vpp-135-or-150mm-travel/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bold Linkin</a> trail to all-mountain bike.</p><h3>Tech details – How does it work?</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081826/2022-Scott-Spark-900-XC-trail-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-cross-country-MTB_internal-headset-routing-cutaway.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081826/2022-Scott-Spark-900-XC-trail-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-cross-country-MTB_internal-headset-routing-cutaway.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Scott Spark RC &amp; 900 XC trail mountain bikes, light fully-integrated cross-country MTB,&nbsp;inside\" width=\"1500\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081826/2022-Scott-Spark-900-XC-trail-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-cross-country-MTB_internal-headset-routing-cutaway.jpg 1500w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081826/2022-Scott-Spark-900-XC-trail-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-cross-country-MTB_internal-headset-routing-cutaway-297x178.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081826/2022-Scott-Spark-900-XC-trail-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-cross-country-MTB_internal-headset-routing-cutaway-800x480.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081826/2022-Scott-Spark-900-XC-trail-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-cross-country-MTB_internal-headset-routing-cutaway-120x72.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081826/2022-Scott-Spark-900-XC-trail-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-cross-country-MTB_internal-headset-routing-cutaway-768x461.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081826/2022-Scott-Spark-900-XC-trail-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-cross-country-MTB_internal-headset-routing-cutaway-696x418.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081826/2022-Scott-Spark-900-XC-trail-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-cross-country-MTB_internal-headset-routing-cutaway-1068x641.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09081826/2022-Scott-Spark-900-XC-trail-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-cross-country-MTB_internal-headset-routing-cutaway-700x420.jpg 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"></a></p><p>In all, Syncros now has five different one-piece carbon iC SL (super light, integrated cockpit) MTB bar shapes to choose from, for a total of 19 sizes to cover cross-country racing to light all-mountain riding. There are even seven separate alloy XC, DC &amp; AM stems that give you the same routing possibilities with conventional bars.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09082004/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_stem-shrouds-internal-cable-routing.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09082004/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_stem-shrouds-internal-cable-routing.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Scott Spark RC &amp; 900 XC trail mountain bikes, light fully-integrated cross-country MTB,&nbsp;headset\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09082004/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_stem-shrouds-internal-cable-routing.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09082004/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_stem-shrouds-internal-cable-routing-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09082004/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_stem-shrouds-internal-cable-routing-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09082004/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_stem-shrouds-internal-cable-routing-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09082004/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_stem-shrouds-internal-cable-routing-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09082004/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_stem-shrouds-internal-cable-routing-696x464.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09082004/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_stem-shrouds-internal-cable-routing-1068x712.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/09082004/2022-Scott-Spark-RC-XC-mountain-bike_light-fully-integrated-carbon-cross-country-MTB_stem-shrouds-internal-cable-routing-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>They all share the same secret – an integrated steerer tube cap, flared covers on both sides of the stem that alloy for cable entry, and integrated steerer tube spacers that split open to guide the cable into your frame in front of/next to/through your headset.</p><p>So far, we’ve only seen these new Syncros bars on Scott/Bold family bikes, but they look to be compatible with any mountain bike that combines a 1.125″ upper steerer (the vast majority of suspension forks on the market) and routing through the headset – like the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/08/18/canyon-spins-unicorn-hair-into-their-lightest-hardtail-ever-with-new-exceed-xc-race-bike/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Canyon Exceed</a> or <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/29/new-bh-lynx-race-carbon-rc-slashes-cost-of-race-proven-xc-downcountry-mountain-bikes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">BH Lynx Race</a>, for example.</p><h3>Syncros Fraser &amp; Hixon iC SL – Sizing, options &amp; pricing</h3><div id=\"attachment_277138\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02125053/2022-Bold-Linkin-integrated-hidden-shock-carbon-trail-bike_135mm-or-150mm-all-mountain-bike_integrated-cockpit.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-277138\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02125053/2022-Bold-Linkin-integrated-hidden-shock-carbon-trail-bike_135mm-or-150mm-all-mountain-bike_integrated-cockpit.jpg\" alt=\"2022 Bold Linkin integrated hidden shock carbon trail bike, 135mm or 150mm all-mountain bike,&nbsp;Syncros Hixon iC SL carbon bar\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02125053/2022-Bold-Linkin-integrated-hidden-shock-carbon-trail-bike_135mm-or-150mm-all-mountain-bike_integrated-cockpit.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02125053/2022-Bold-Linkin-integrated-hidden-shock-carbon-trail-bike_135mm-or-150mm-all-mountain-bike_integrated-cockpit-297x167.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02125053/2022-Bold-Linkin-integrated-hidden-shock-carbon-trail-bike_135mm-or-150mm-all-mountain-bike_integrated-cockpit-800x450.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02125053/2022-Bold-Linkin-integrated-hidden-shock-carbon-trail-bike_135mm-or-150mm-all-mountain-bike_integrated-cockpit-120x68.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02125053/2022-Bold-Linkin-integrated-hidden-shock-carbon-trail-bike_135mm-or-150mm-all-mountain-bike_integrated-cockpit-768x432.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-277138\">c. Bold</p></div><p>From a cockpit perspective, the result is potentially cleaner internal cable routing. Theoretically, it also means lighter and stronger frames when you don’t have to cut out holes in the head or downtubes to get cables in for internal routing, plus the end of cable rub on your frame.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155906/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar-top.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155906/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar-top.jpg\" alt=\"Syncros Fraser iC SL DC bar top\" width=\"2000\" height=\"400\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155906/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar-top.jpg 2000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155906/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar-top-297x59.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155906/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar-top-800x160.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155906/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar-top-120x24.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155906/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar-top-768x154.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155906/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar-top-1536x307.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\"></a></p><p>For the cross/downcountry racer there are the most options. The 350€ Syncros Fraser iC SL bars all feature 6° upsweep and 8° backsweep. Syncros describes the varied combination of virtual stem angle &amp; length as a “new geometry concept” so a rider’s grip height doesn’t change, no matter the length you pick.</p><div id=\"attachment_277197\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155903/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-WC-XC-bars.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-277197\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155903/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-WC-XC-bars.jpg\" alt=\"Syncros Fraser iC SL WC &amp; XC bars\" width=\"2200\" height=\"1225\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155903/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-WC-XC-bars.jpg 2200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155903/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-WC-XC-bars-297x165.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155903/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-WC-XC-bars-800x445.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155903/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-WC-XC-bars-120x67.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155903/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-WC-XC-bars-768x428.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155903/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-WC-XC-bars-1536x855.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155903/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-WC-XC-bars-2048x1140.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2200px) 100vw, 2200px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-277197\">Syncros Fraser iC SL WC -40, -30, -20 &amp; XC bars</p></div><p>The 740mm wide flat bars come in six WC sizes with steeper World Cup fits like Nino, Kate &amp; the Scott SRAM racing pros ride (-40°/80 or 90mm, -30°/90 or 100mm, or -20°/90 or 100mm). Or you can get a less aggressive XC fit in five sizes of the less drop cross-country model (-14°/50mm, -12°/60, -10°/70, -9°/80, -8°/90).</p><div id=\"attachment_277196\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155900/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-277196\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155900/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar.jpg\" alt=\"Syncros Fraser iC SL DC bar\" width=\"2200\" height=\"549\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155900/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar.jpg 2200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155900/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar-297x74.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155900/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar-800x200.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155900/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar-120x30.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155900/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar-768x192.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155900/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar-1536x383.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155900/Syncros-Fraser-iC-SL-DC-bar-2048x511.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2200px) 100vw, 2200px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-277196\">Syncros Fraser iC SL DC bar</p></div><p>A slightly wider 760mm downcountry mini riser bar version adds 8mm of rise in four DC fits (0°/50, 60, 70, or 80mm).</p><div id=\"attachment_277195\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155857/Syncros-Hixon-iC-SL-riser-bars.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-277195\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155857/Syncros-Hixon-iC-SL-riser-bars.jpg\" alt=\"Syncros Hixon iC SL riser bar\" width=\"2200\" height=\"750\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155857/Syncros-Hixon-iC-SL-riser-bars.jpg 2200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155857/Syncros-Hixon-iC-SL-riser-bars-297x101.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155857/Syncros-Hixon-iC-SL-riser-bars-800x273.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155857/Syncros-Hixon-iC-SL-riser-bars-120x41.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155857/Syncros-Hixon-iC-SL-riser-bars-768x262.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155857/Syncros-Hixon-iC-SL-riser-bars-1536x524.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155857/Syncros-Hixon-iC-SL-riser-bars-2048x698.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2200px) 100vw, 2200px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-277195\">Syncros Hixon iC SL 15 &amp; 25 riser bars</p></div><p>Trail and All-Mountain riders get a couple of wider options for the same price. The 350€ Syncros Hixon iC SL get the same 6° upsweep,&nbsp; and incrementally less 7° backsweep. A 780mm wide, low-riser trail bar gets 15mm of rise in two sizes (5°/50 or 4°/60mm). The widest 800mm mid-riser bar gets 25mm of rise in two sizes (5°/50 or 4°/60mm).</p><div id=\"attachment_277194\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155854/Syncros-iC-SL-bar_photo-by-Daniel-Geiger_Spark-RC-World-Cup-AXS-detail.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-277194\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155854/Syncros-iC-SL-bar_photo-by-Daniel-Geiger_Spark-RC-World-Cup-AXS-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Syncros Fraser &amp; Hixon iC SL integrated cockpit MTB bars\" width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155854/Syncros-iC-SL-bar_photo-by-Daniel-Geiger_Spark-RC-World-Cup-AXS-detail.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155854/Syncros-iC-SL-bar_photo-by-Daniel-Geiger_Spark-RC-World-Cup-AXS-detail-297x167.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155854/Syncros-iC-SL-bar_photo-by-Daniel-Geiger_Spark-RC-World-Cup-AXS-detail-800x450.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155854/Syncros-iC-SL-bar_photo-by-Daniel-Geiger_Spark-RC-World-Cup-AXS-detail-120x68.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155854/Syncros-iC-SL-bar_photo-by-Daniel-Geiger_Spark-RC-World-Cup-AXS-detail-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155854/Syncros-iC-SL-bar_photo-by-Daniel-Geiger_Spark-RC-World-Cup-AXS-detail-1536x864.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-277194\">c. Scott, photo by Daniel Geiger</p></div><p>All feature the same removable stem cover to hide all of your cables, and feature direct-mount bolts under the front of the stem where you can attach a Syncros out-front bracket to mount a GPS, a GoPro action cam, or a headlight for night riding.</p><div id=\"attachment_277193\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155851/Syncros-iC-SL-cockpit-on-an-e-bike_photo-by-Jochen-Haar_Scott-Patron-Bosch-Kiox-eMTB.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-277193\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155851/Syncros-iC-SL-cockpit-on-an-e-bike_photo-by-Jochen-Haar_Scott-Patron-Bosch-Kiox-eMTB.jpg\" alt=\"Syncros Fraser &amp; Hixon iC SL integrated cockpit eMTB bars\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1000\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155851/Syncros-iC-SL-cockpit-on-an-e-bike_photo-by-Jochen-Haar_Scott-Patron-Bosch-Kiox-eMTB.jpg 1500w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155851/Syncros-iC-SL-cockpit-on-an-e-bike_photo-by-Jochen-Haar_Scott-Patron-Bosch-Kiox-eMTB-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155851/Syncros-iC-SL-cockpit-on-an-e-bike_photo-by-Jochen-Haar_Scott-Patron-Bosch-Kiox-eMTB-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155851/Syncros-iC-SL-cockpit-on-an-e-bike_photo-by-Jochen-Haar_Scott-Patron-Bosch-Kiox-eMTB-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155851/Syncros-iC-SL-cockpit-on-an-e-bike_photo-by-Jochen-Haar_Scott-Patron-Bosch-Kiox-eMTB-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-277193\">c. Scott, photo by Jochen Haar</p></div><p>Plus, you can use custom-fit Syncros top cap mounts that work with standard cycling computers, or even e-bike displays.</p><div id=\"attachment_277192\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155847/Syncros-iC-SL-cockpit_photo-by-Jochen-Haar_Scott-Spark-900-Tuned.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-277192\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155847/Syncros-iC-SL-cockpit_photo-by-Jochen-Haar_Scott-Spark-900-Tuned.jpg\" alt=\"Syncros Fraser &amp; Hixon iC SL integrated cockpit MTB bars\" width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155847/Syncros-iC-SL-cockpit_photo-by-Jochen-Haar_Scott-Spark-900-Tuned.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155847/Syncros-iC-SL-cockpit_photo-by-Jochen-Haar_Scott-Spark-900-Tuned-297x167.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155847/Syncros-iC-SL-cockpit_photo-by-Jochen-Haar_Scott-Spark-900-Tuned-800x450.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155847/Syncros-iC-SL-cockpit_photo-by-Jochen-Haar_Scott-Spark-900-Tuned-120x68.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155847/Syncros-iC-SL-cockpit_photo-by-Jochen-Haar_Scott-Spark-900-Tuned-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/02155847/Syncros-iC-SL-cockpit_photo-by-Jochen-Haar_Scott-Spark-900-Tuned-1536x864.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-277192\">c. Scott, photo by Jochen Haar</p></div><p><a href=\"https://www.syncros.com/gb/en/integrated-cockpit\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Syncros.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"b954d2c615172d25ace7a2fc8dd62c76754d8ae